title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi \colon  A\to  {\mathopen {}\left  [2\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00LO.xml"
addr="jms-00LO"
title="Predicate">predicate</fr:link> on a set <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>. The <fr:em><fr:strong>comprehension</fr:strong></fr:em> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi ]]></fr:tex> is defined to be the following subset <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [\phi \right  ]\mathclose {}}\subseteq  A]]></fr:tex> spanned by elements at which <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi ]]></fr:tex> holds, as specified below:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[  {\mathopen {}\left  [\phi \right  ]\mathclose {}} = {\mathopen {}\left \{a\in  A\,\middle \vert \,\phi {\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=1\right \}\mathclose {}} ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>